	<h2>Recipes</h2>

	@* recipe 1 *@
	<h3>1. Chocolate Chip Cookies</h3>
	<p>These cookies are soft, chewy, and packed with chocolate chips.</p>
	<ul>
		<li>2 1/4 cups all-purpose flour</li>
		<li>1 teaspoon baking soda</li>
		<li>1/2 teaspoon salt</li>
		<li>1 cup unsalted butter, melted</li>
		<li>3/4 cup brown sugar</li>
		<li>3/4 cup white sugar</li>
		<li>2 teaspoons vanilla extract</li>
		<li>2 large eggs</li>
		<li>2 cups chocolate chips</li>
	</ul>
	@* instructions *@
	<p>Mix ingredients, scoop onto a baking sheet, and bake at 350°F (175°C) for 10-12 minutes.</p>
	@* image *@
	<img src="~/images/cookies.jpg" alt="Cookies" style="width: 200px; height: auto; margin-bottom:25px" />

	@* recipe 2 *@
	<h3>2. Pancakes</h3>
	<p>These pancakes are light, fluffy, and perfect for breakfast.</p>
	<ul>
		<li>1 1/2 cups all-purpose flour</li>
		<li>3 1/2 teaspoons baking powder</li>
		<li>1 teaspoon salt</li>
		<li>1 tablespoon sugar</li>
		<li>1 1/4 cups milk</li>
		<li>1 egg</li>
		<li>3 tablespoons melted butter</li>
	</ul>
	@* instructions *@
	<p>Whisk everything together and cook on a hot griddle until golden brown.</p>
	@* image *@
	<img src="~/images/pancakes.jpg" alt="Pancakes" style="width: 200px; height: auto; margin-bottom:25px" />
	<br />

	@* recipe 3 *@
	<h3>3. Banana Bread</h3>
	<p>A moist and flavorful banana bread that makes a great snack or breakfast.</p>
	<ul>
		<li>2-3 ripe bananas, mashed</li>
		<li>1/3 cup melted butter</li>
		<li>1 cup sugar</li>
		<li>1 egg, beaten</li>
		<li>1 teaspoon vanilla extract</li>
		<li>1 teaspoon baking soda</li>
		<li>Pinch of salt</li>
		<li>1 1/2 cups all-purpose flour</li>
	</ul>
	@* instructions *@
	<p>Mix ingredients, pour into a greased loaf pan, and bake at 350°F (175°C) for 50-60 minutes.</p>
